replies.body:
The path to excellence is to play at least 50 games with every character in blind, normals, or Aram before playing ranked. That way you have a general understanding of each character, each position, and each role. The game isn't as much about how well you play your character as it is how well you know the character the enemy is using. This is a colorful game of chess: those who know the most moves and strategies and match ups will win the most. 

Time to study. 

{{sticker:sona-playing}}
